FITROTSEARCH(1)	     				               FITROTSEARCH(1)

NNAAMMEE
  fitrotsearch - determine minimum in fit to output from matchrotpairs

SSYYNNOOPPSSIISS
  fitrotsearch [options] input_file

DDEESSCCRRIIPPTTIIOONN
  Fitrotsearch fits a 3-dimensional polynomial to the difference measures
  output by Matchrotpairs(1) and reports the minimum of the fit.  When a
  relatively thin sample is used to obtain the pairs of images being matched,
  the pair that gives the minimum may not be the best matching pair, because
  of variability in the difference measure.  Fitting to the data and
  measuring the minimum from the fit will give a more accurate assessment of
  the best matching pair.  If a different best pair is determined from this
  fit, then you should rerun Matchrotpairs with just this pair to get the
  appropriate transformation between rotated images.

  Fitrotsearch uses the PIP package for input exclusively (see the manual
  page for pip(1)).  The following options can be specified either as command
  line arguments (with the -) or one per line in a command file or parameter
  file (without the -):

INSERT OPTION TEXT HERE

  -StandardInput
     Read parameter entries from standard input.

